y you will hit more often , for less damage, rather than less for more damage, eh ?<br><br>Proc weapons like a ykesha help maintain aggro too. I have a bard that can easily outaggro most tanks with dual ykeshas... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/uginweil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ginweil</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.wi.rr.com/ginweil/ivicon_copy.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/24/02 11:01:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.wi.rr.com/ginweil/ivicon_copy.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wurmslayer vs. Lammy/Centi</span><hr size=1> Less delay = more agro. More agro = Less the Ranger has to die. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center>Ginweil Splitfeather58 Outrider - Infinitus Vindicat<BR><img src="http://home.wi.rr.com/ginweil/GinSigNew.jpg"</img><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=24277">View Equipment</a></center><br><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=38488">Resist Equip</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/uglorfendill.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glorfendill</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/28/02 2:48:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wurmslayer vs. Lammy/Centi</span><hr size=1> But at the same point, Glorf my 45 War can normally out Agro anyone I group with any time his Runebladed sword of night procs.. 12/26 +3 STA/STR 176dd proc... so if you have a good Dex, break out a nice proc weapon and you can normally get all the agro you can handle. So My suggestion.. just because every twink in the world has 2 lammy's a cent, and a wurmy.. doesn't mean those are the best weapons to use ;-) <p><A HREF="http://blog.ravenblack.net/quiz/videogame.pl"><IMG BORDER=0 ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=80 SRC="http://blog.ravenblack.net/quiz/videogame/17.png" ALT="What Video Game Character Are You? I am Mario." /></A>I am <B>Mario</B>.<BR /><BR />I like to jump around, and would lead a fairly serene and aimless existence if it weren't for my friends always getting into trouble. I love to help out, even when it puts me at risk. I seem to make friends with people who just can't stay out of trouble. <A HREF="http://blog.ravenblack.net/quiz/videogame.pl">What Video Game Character Are You?</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ushaorinorsoulbringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shaorinor Soulbringer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/29/02 6:32:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wurmslayer vs. Lammy/Centi</span><hr size=1> Low delay weapon should always be in the primary hand.<br><br>Wurmslayer is the devil...I really hate that weapon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/binfinitusvindicat.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sunny>sunny</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/31/02 12:56:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wurmslayer vs. Lammy/Centi</span><hr size=1> in the early 40's i still find my warrior outdmging rogues and rangers quite badly.  Of course this is against the grain, rogues are to be the supreme bad arse dmg dealers, and rangers are to deal more dmg than warriors. <br><br>maybe it's equipment differences, but im thinking until you hit 50 ish then wear your wurmy with pride.  Not only can you do serious dmg with it, but you can keep agro fine if the ranger doesn't taunt (grrrr to that ranger who does taunt) <br><br>GRanted, in a raid situation i guess you want agro agro agro so use the lammy.  Dmg in a raid isn't based off one warrior anyway, so sacrifice the dmg for the delay in that case.  Hopefully the mean of the rogues out there will catch up in dmg by 50's so you can do your job, which is to stand there and get beat on.  Note i said &quot;mean&quot; of rogues, we've all seen the twinked buggers runnin around bsing for incredible numbers early on /COUGH FARGLING  :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=569.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=569.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.infinitusvindicat.com/images/f_addreply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=569.top